  "id": "019d32c6-ee5c-7430-ac49-f15fe97dd493",
  "content": "# Research Spike Correction: Agent Teams Identity Correlation (Verified)\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-28\n**Supersedes:** Previous spike finding about env vars and joinedAt correlation\n\n## Key Correction: Teammate Identity is Fully Solvable\n\nThe earlier brainstorm assumed we needed env vars on teammate processes to identify them. The spike proved this wrong. Teammates have NO team-specific env vars. But we don't need them.\n\n## Verified Identity Chain\n\n1. **config.json** has `leadSessionId` (bridges team to lead's session) and member `name`s with `agentId` format `{name}@{team-name}` (deterministic)\n2. **Lead's transcript** has `teamName` field on every entry while team is active, plus Agent tool calls with `name` (teammate name) and `team_name`\n3. **Teammate transcripts** live at `{leadSessionId}/subagents/agent-{id}.jsonl` under the lead's session directory\n4. **First message** of each teammate transcript contains `<teammate-message teammate_id=\"team-lead\">` with the full spawn prompt\n5. **TeammateIdle hook** provides `teammate_name` + `team_name` on stdin (fires on the lead's process)\n6. **TaskCreated/TaskCompleted hooks** provide `task_id`, `task_subject`, `session_id` (lead's)\n\n## Dynamic Team Membership\n\nTeammates CAN be spawned at any time (not just at team creation). `joinedAt` in config.json is NOT reliable for batch-spawn correlation (1-2s gaps, ambiguous). But this doesn't matter because the transcript-based and hook-based identity chains don't depend on timing.\n\n## Revised Correlation Strategy\n\nNo need for env vars, timing heuristics, or mapping files. The hooks (especially TeammateIdle) give us teammate_name + team_name directly. The lead's transcript gives us the full subagent-to-teammate mapping. The adapter reads both sources.\n\n## What Still Needs Verification\n\nThe identity chain must be tested with:\n- Late-joining teammates (spawned mid-session)\n- Teammates that spawn their own subagents (3-level deep)\n- Teammates that crash without graceful shutdown\n- Multiple teams in sequence (same lead session, clean up and recreate)\n",
